	<Header validationStatus="Unknown" version="1.0" date="2026-07-17T00:00:00Z">
		<NoteSet>
			<Note>ST[15] On-Board Storage and Retrieval. See pus_analysis/pus15.md and
				pus_simulator_architecture.md for the full design rationale.</Note>
			<Note>Core lifecycle scope only: packet store CRUD (TC[15,20/21/22/23/25/28]), storage
				enable/disable (TC[15,1/2] + TM[15,19]), summary reporting (TC[15,12] + TM[15,13]),
				by-time-range retrieval (TC[15,9/17]) and open retrieval (TC[15,14/15/16]). The Packet
				Selection subservice (TC[15,3/4/5/6] and the HK/diagnostic/event filter tables,
				TC[15,29-40]) is deferred -- see Pus15Service javadoc for the pass-all storage default
				used in the meantime. TC[15,24/26/27] are out of scope per pus15.md.</Note>
			<Note>All packet-store state (stores map, fill tracking, retrieval threads) lives on-board
				(emulated by Pus15Service in the simulator). This MDB only encodes the TC[15,x]
				configuration/retrieval commands and decodes the TM[15,13]/[15,19]/[15,23] reports.</Note>
			<Note>Timestamps (TC[15,9] start_time/end_time, TC[15,11] time_limit, TC[15,14] start_time,
				TM[15,13] oldest_ts/newest_ts/open_retrieval_start_time) are a raw unsigned 64-bit
				milliseconds value, not a CUC-encoded field -- see pus15.md Gap 1. Pus15Service compares
				these directly against its internal packet-store timestamps (also raw millis).</Note>
			<Note>Several TCs accept either N specific store ids or "all stores" (zero-byte payload) --
				XTCE cannot express optional arguments, so each is split into a "_SPECIFIC" and "_ALL"
				MetaCommand pair (Gap 2). Pus15Service disambiguates at runtime via
				bb.remaining()==0. Affected subtypes: 1, 2, 12, 14, 15, 16, 17, 21. TC[15,14]'s "all"
				variant additionally means "all suspended stores" (silently filtered); a store id
				named explicitly in the "_SPECIFIC" variant that isn't suspended is rejected.</Note>
			<Note>store_type and vc_id are always included as fixed fields in TC[15,20]/TM[15,23]
				(mission convention, see pus15.md Gap 4) rather than modelled as optional.</Note>
		</NoteSet>
	</Header>
